  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "Create a program that simulates a to-do list manager using a queue. \n\nThe program should allow users to perform the following operations:\n\n\nAdd a task to the to-do list.\nIf the task is already present in the list - then ignore the task\nDisplay the current to-do list once all tasks have been added\nThe code given here has implemented queues using arrays. \n\nUpdate the code to solve the problem.",
    "constraints": [
      "1 <= T <= 10",
      "1 <= N <= 10",
      "1 <= task <= 1000"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "First line contains an integer T, the number of test cases. Each test case starts with an integer N, the number of tasks to be added. The next N lines each contain a single integer task (1 ≤ task ≤ 1000).",
    "outputFormat": "For each test case, print the distinct tasks in the order of their first appearance, each on its own line. Do not print extra blank lines between test cases.",
